text: Yaseen Khalil Abdullah al-Sheyadi (; born 5 February 1994), commonly known as Yaseen al-Sheyadi, is an Omani footballer who plays for Al-Suwaiq Club. ==Club career== On 8 August 2014, he signed a one-year contract with Al-Suwaiq Club. ===Club career statistics=== {| class="wikitable" style="text-align: center;" |- !rowspan="2"|Club !rowspan="2"|Season !rowspan="2"|Division !colspan="2"|League !colspan="2"|Cup !colspan="2"|ContinentalIncludes appearances in the AFC Cup !colspan="2"|Other !colspan="2"|Total |- !Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals |- |rowspan="3"|Al-Suwaiq |2011–12 |rowspan="2"|Oman Professional League ||-||1||-||0||0||0||-||0||-||1 |- |2013–14 ||-||0||-||0||3||0||-||0||-||0 |- !colspan="2"|Total !-!!1!!-!!0!!3!!0!!-!!0!!-!!1 |- !colspan="3"|Career total !-!!1!!-!!0!!3!!0!!-!!0!!-!!1 |} ==International career== Yaseen was selected for the national team for the first time in 2014. He made his first appearance for Oman on 30 May 2015, in a friendly match against Bahrain.
